# MIniWall backend app with nodejs express

This is an app that provides API endpoints for users in a social media platform.
Users can create/edit posts, like and comment on others post.

# Stack

Nodejs Express, MongoDB

# File Structure

- app.js --> The express app.
- config (folder) --> Configuration files.
- models --> Monggose schemas.
- routes --> API endpoints.
- middleware --> Middlewares for request i.e. authentication.
- controllers --> Middlewares that control the response of an API.
- helpers (folder) --> Reusable helper functions.

# Running the App

To run the backend use npm start. Runs on port 8080.

